		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>Results of a study of the worst case learning curves for a particular class of probability distribution on input space to MLP with hard threshold hidden units are presented. It is shown in particular , that in the thermodynamic limit for scaling by the number of connections to the first hidden layer, although the true learning curve behaves as ~ a-I for a ~ 1, its VC-dimension based bound is trivial (= 1) and its VC-entropy bound is trivial for a ::; 6.2. It is also shown that bounds following the true learning curve can be derived from a formalism based on the density of error patterns.</p>
			</abstract>
